ws]]|[[Josh Fountain]]|[[Stella Rose Bennett]]}}\n|producer={{hlist|Josh Fountain|Brendan Patrick Rice}}\n|chronology=[[Benee]]\n|prev_title=[[Monsta (song)|Monsta]]\n|prev_year=2019\n|year=2019\n|misc={{external music video|type=single|{{YouTube|Rb6Scz-5YOs|Supalonely}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Supalonely'''\" is a song by New Zealand musician [[Benee]]. It was initially released as a song on her second extended play ''[[Stella & Steve]]'' on 15 November 2019, before becoming the EP's third and final single on 6 December 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pilerats.com/written/light-easy/must-listen-singles-benee-spacey-jane-young-franco-more/|title=This Week's Must-Listen Singles: BENEE, Spacey Jane, Young Franco + more|last=Davies|first=Hayden|date=11 December 2019|website=PILERATS|url-status=live|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref> The song gained popularity after spawning a viral dance challenge on the online video-sharing platform [[TikTok]] in March 2020.<ref name=\"Idolator\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7907879/future-hit-benees-supalonely-is-absolutely-irresistible|title=Future Hit: BENEE's \"Supalonely\" Is Absolutely Irresistible|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=10 March 2020|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|url-status=live|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/videos/benees-supalonely-is-ultra-infectious|title=BENEE's 'Supalonely' Is Ultra-Infectious|last=Murray|first=Robin|date=6 March 2020|website=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> The song peaked on charts of countries such as United Kingdom, Netherlands, Norway, Sweden and Ireland. The song entered the Top 40 of both the US and Global [[Spotify Velocity|Spotify Charts]], where on 10 March alone it gained 662,000 streams in the US and 1.84 million streams globally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2020/03/11/benee-gus-dappertons-supalonely-reaches-new-peak-on-spotify-chart-enters-top-100-on-us-itunes-sales-chart/|title=BENEE & Gus Dapperton's \"Supalonely\" Reaches New Peak On Spotify Chart, Enters Top 100 On US iTunes Sales Chart|last=Cantor|first=Brian|date=11 March 2020|website=Headline Planet|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\nOn his [[Apple Music]] show, [[Elton John]] described \"Supalonely\" as a \"smash record\", and further described Benee as \"an amazing young artist\" who \"writes really brilliantly\".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Barton|first=Monika|url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/entertainment/2020/03/elton-john-raves-about-amazing-benee-confesses-he-s-crazy-about-six60-on-apple-music-show.html|title=Elton John raves about 'amazing' Benee, confesses he's 'crazy about' Six60 on Apple Music show|date=6 March 2020|work=Newshub|access-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live|language=en}}</ref> Ariana Marsh from [[I-D|''i-D'']] wrote that the \"sunny pop\" song \"turns your typical breakup song on its head\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_uk/article/jgeg8b/benee-and-gus-dapperton-turn-breakup-blues-into-sunny-pop-on-supalonely|title=BENEE and Gus Dapperton turn breakup blues into sunny pop on Supalonely|last=Marsh|first=Ariana|date=4 February 2020|website=[[i-D]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref> The song was described by Glenn Rowley of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' as \"a quirky, knowing ode to the art of loneliness.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8550207/benee-supalonely-video-tour-dates|title=Benee Is 'Supalonely' in Colorful New Video, Announces North American Tour: See the Dates|last=Rowley|first=Glenn|date=5 February 2020|website=Billboard|url-status=live|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref name=\"ARIA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/